snippet.title: Lower Rhine - From Düsseldorf to Emmerich | Discover Germany
snippet.description:
Lower Rhine - From Düsseldorf to Emmerich | Discover Germany
Toegevoegd door DW (English) laatste augustus
The northernmost stretch of the Rhine in Germany takes the river through the largest of Germany's federal states: North Rhine-Westphalia. Our trip on what's called the Lower Rhine begins in its capital, Düsseldorf. The 180 kilometer stretch of the Rhine between Bonn and Emmerich is called the Lower Rhine. The Rhine is one of Europe's most important waterways. Many of the ports on its banks were created as early as the Middle Ages. Read more: http://www.dw.de/program/discover-germany/s-7856-9798

snippet.title: Death Toll From Washington Landslide Rises To 41
snippet.description:
Death Toll From Washington Landslide Rises To 41
Toegevoegd door wochit vorig maandag
The death toll from last month's landslide in Washington state has risen to 41. That's up two from Wednesday, when the Snohomish County Medical Examiner's Office updated the news media on recovery efforts. A rain-saturated hillside along the Stillaguamish River gave way on the outskirts of the rural town of Oso on March 22. Search crews have been digging through deep mud and debris, which is 70 feet thick in some places, to search for the missing.
